values:
So, tell me what you think!

All comments screened.

Note: All written for , for the Drabble Meme. Prompt: Automail Woes Winry ran her hands over the toolbox before using her thumbs to flip the latches up. She pushed the lid open, looking inside at the array of tools, all in perfect order, all gleaming, shiny and new. Lifting the tray, she surveyed the rows of socket heads with their wrench, star drivers, screwdrivers. Winry picked up the three-sixteenths socket, holding it up to eye level and looking through it before setting it back in its place. She replaced the tray and closed the lid, latching the toolbox closed. New tools, all perfect for working on automail. And there was no automail to work on. * * * Prompts: A snowplow, a mask, and some carrots "Perfect, Thomas, thanks." Winry waved at him, knowing her voice wouldn't carry. Cutting the engine to the snowplow, he leaned his elbows out the window of his Hummer. "I don't suppose you'd like to give me a clue what you're doing?" Winry hummed to herself, starting rolling the snow. She pushed down the scarf she was using to mask her mouth, to keep the air warm as it entered her lungs. "Making a snow man. Why else would I ask you to bring me carrots?" note: Thomas is Thomas Raith, another character in Second City. * * * Prompts: Apple Pie and Ice Cream The apple pie sat on the counter, steaming softly. At the table, Winry leaned her chin in her hand, waiting for the scent to bring them thundering into the kitchen. "Al? Ed?" she called, when she didn't hear them coming. "I made pie. I even got you ice cream, Al." The apartment remained silent, no cheerful voices, no one shouting that he'd be right there. Winry stared at the pie, watching as it cooled and eventually stopped steaming before she rose, pushing her chair back under the table carefully, and left the room. * * *
Anything prior to this post was for <lj user=gateways_2_dawn>.

I woke up a little early and borrowed this from
cornerofmadness
- anagram generator.

I don't think I like my anagram: 

'nowhere winry'
anagrams to
'Wry, new heroin.'

I am so angry right now, I can barely type.  What in the world was Ed thinking?  I know he thought he was helping but that...offer...the way he made it - GAH!  If there's a professor I could have talked to, I'm sure I could've gotten myself some time in the shop, especially after I showed off my blueprints.  I know how to sweet talk mechanics.  I know the language.  If I couldn't go through the school, then I'd go off campus and talk to some of the mechanics there. 

The thing is, I'm not really sure I belong at this school, anyway.  Pre-med?  I don't think it's for me.  I mean, I remember reading my parents' medical books all the time as a kid and I still like looking at them but I really prefer biomechanics.  I want to make limbs for people who need them and I'm already worried, since Ed's telling me that Audey was doing work on his automail - that I already know more than what anyone can teach me here.

Maybe I really need to just be working instead of at the college. 

I'll have to think on that and try to make a decision.  I don't want to be taking up space in a school where I'm not going to learn anything. 

I guess I should get ready to go to the martial arts class.  I'm just going to sit and watch with Willow and Athena, though.  ...And I guess once it's over, I'll talk to Ed. 

Oh.  And we're supposed to go out in the woods tonight, too.  Wonder how we can slip past Ara, since she'll be at the class?  Hmmm, something to think about.  A mystery, like Haru'd say.

<font size="3">Other things to ask me?  Um...well, I remember sleeping in class a lot when I was a kid. Funny, I don't remember going to class much after my eleventh birthday.  Isn't that weird?  Granny home schooled me.  </font>

...Do not ever, ever, ever let Edward Elric mess around with his prostheses.  

Goku, if you want to continue our conversation, I'm here!
<font size="3">I love my new journal layout!  Thank you, Ed!  </font>

It seems like it's been a really long day.  A lot of things have happened since I woke up this morning - I've met a lot of new people already!  Funny thing, one of them is a boy I remember knowing as a kid.  For the most part, everyone seems friendly and helpful, even if some of the professors are a bit...odd.  I mean, Professor Pan just let us go after about fifteen minutes!  Didn't assign homework or anything.  I guess I'll see how tomorrow's class goes.

I feel very clumsy here, too.  I fell down twice!  It's like I can't keep my feet under me.  I'm going to have so many bruises if I can't get my 'sea legs'.  

Willow's staying the night in my room tonight.  She's very sweet.  The reason Willow's here is because I got dizzy, just all of a sudden, and haven't been feeling quite right since.  A nurse even came and checked me out.  She gave me some pills to take.  

And that's where one of the weird things happened.  The boy, Ed?  Edward Elric.  He just seems so familiar, a lot more familiar than if I hadn't seen him since we were kids.  He's cute, too, a bit intense but still cute.  He makes me feel...I don't know.  Comfortable?  It's hard to explain.  Anyway, he was there when the nurse came into my dorm and he kind of freaked out.  He got very upset with the R.A., Ara Al-Sayid, and the nurse, too, because they kept talking about taking me away and running tests.  It might've been sweet if I hadn't been feeling terrible at the time.  And then, after the nurse gave me some pills to take,  Ed stole them and flushed them down the toilet!  And when his roommate, Audey, came to check on us, Ed kissed me.  

I nearly slapped him.  I mean, who did he think he was, just kissing me like that?  Ed even timed it so that Audey would see and then, after I got the door closed again, told me that he didn't want me to wind up like him.  I just feel so confused. 
 
I hope tomorrow isn't quite so exciting.

I think I'm relieved to know you wear boxers, Ed.  The idea of you running around commando...or in leather...just...disturbs me.  Goku, you're bad.  I don't think I'll be imagining anyone in any underwear, okay? 

...WAIT!!! THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEAN!  *whines*

"Oh... Cider is very good. It's made from apples. Auntie usually made two batches. One that was fermented into hard cider, and one that wasn't so us kids could drink it.

Even if I remember the details differently, I do remember the incident. I think all three of us threw up, but I got the worst end and threw up most of the next day too. [snort] Leave it to me to overindulge in something more than anyone else. Lately, I find I prefer Cognac. Europe's drinking laws are not puritanical like here," Ed explained. 

"I don't know what that is either. I like sake. Puri...huh? that means we can't drink right?" Goku asked.

Puritanical?  That just sounds unpleasant.  Umm...Ed?  I don't remember the three of us drinking the hard cider.  I remember you and me drinking it and A...Alphonse...taking care of us.  And Granny laughing because we'd made ourselves so sick.  

Isn't that strange?

I think I'm going to like college.  I've met some really wonderful people so far, well; they certainly seem wonderful under the first impressions rule.  Granny would probably smack me for deciding that I should be friends with them without checking them out more thoroughly but I've got to go with my instincts, right?  They've never led me wrong before.  

I found out that one of the girls I met today is a missing roommate!  Her name is Fuu.  I can't pronounce her last name at all.  Her clothing sense is amazing.  I know for a fact I wouldn't want to wear the things she wears - well, maybe that skirt.  *grin* 

My first class was strange; Professor Pan is teaching English Lit.  I got to class a few minutes late and he decided to take us outside instead.  By the time we'd gotten out of the third floor classroom and out into the quad, he'd decided he'd had enough or something, and dismissed us.  It was very strange.  But that's where I met two - maybe three! - of my new friends, Goku Son (or is it Son Goku?  I don't understand how his name runs), who's hyperactive and sweet and did I mention hyperactive?  I think someone's convinced him he's stupid, too, which is just sad.  He seems starved for attention, like a puppy who's been left alone too long.  One of the girls in class is Susan Pevensie?  I'm not sure if I spelled her name right.  She got crushed between Goku and the wall when he took us all out sliding around the corner. 

And I got my first cell phone.  Oak Phone?  I'm not sure about that, either.  It's neat, a little lavendar thing that supposedly does everything except go to classes for me (and Haru-kun - another of the people I met today - says that I could get a personal recorder for that - I wish I had a clue what he meant by it - am I paying someone to attend my classes?).  Anyway, I've got Goku's, Fuu's, Haru's and Ed's numbers programmed into the phone already.  Now, if I can remember how to use it when I need it.  

And before I forget (as if I would), I've met someone who seems far too familiar and I'm not sure if I should smack him upside the head or hug him.  His name is Edward Elric and there's something about him I just can't pin down.  If I believed in reincarnation, I'd think that we'd known each other very well in a past life but that can't be right, can it?

Professor Hawkeye, I made this for you: 


...and has anyone seen the chemistry professor, Mustang?
<font size="3">Someone says I don't update my journal enough.  I think, if someone wants to talk to me, he should just open his mouth and talk.  </font>
